    <title>Expressing the sense of Congress that the use of offensive military force by a President without prior and clear authorization of an Act of Congress constitutes an impeachable high crime and misdemeanor under article II, section 4 of the Constitution.</title>
    <cboCostEstimates />
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2013-01-03</actionDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2013-01-09T15:57:18Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Expresses the sense of Congress that, except in response to an actual or imminent attack against the United States, the use of offensive military force by a President without prior and clear authorization of an Act of Congress violates the exclusive power of Congress to declare war under article I of the Constitution, and therefore constitutes an impeachable high crime and misdemeanor under article II.</p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <updateDate>2013-01-03T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
        </item>
